{{Infobox Hieroglyphen
|NAME = <hiero>V31:n:n:n N14-N33-N33-N33</hiero>
|NAME-TRANSKRIPTION = Kenemu<br/>''Knmw''<br/>''The Dark Ken-Stars''
}}

'''Kenemu''' is the designation of an {{ill|Ancient Egypt|de|Altes Ägypten|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Decade (Ancient Egypt)|de|Dekade (Altägypten)|1=Decan|12=draft|12=draft}}, which comprised three {{ill|Baktiu|de|Baktiu|12=draft|12=draft}} (decan stars). The name of the decan is derived from its faint {{ill|Star|de|Stern|12=draft|12=draft}}s, and this celestial region appears as a "dark spot."

The most prominent stars associated with this decan are [[:en:Alpha_Serpentis|Alpha Serpentis]] in the {{ill|Serpens (constellation)|de|Schlange (Sternbild)|12=draft|12=draft}} constellation and {{ill|Hydor|de|Hydor|12=draft|12=draft}} in the {{ill|Aquarius (constellation)|de|Wassermann (Sternbild)|12=draft|12=draft}} constellation.

In the decan lists of the {{ill|Book of Nut#Pharaonic period|lt=Pharaonic period|de|Nutbuch#Pharaonische Zeit}}, Kenemu represented the 16th decan on the body of {{ill|Nut (Egyptian mythology)|de|Nut (Ägyptische Mythologie)|1=Nut (goddess)|lt=Nut|12=draft|12=draft}}. The {{ill|Heliacal rising|de|Heliakisch|12=draft|12=draft}} was set for the {{ill|Achet#Dating|lt=6th Achet II|de|6. Achet II}}, based on the arrangement ordered under {{ill|Senusret III|de|Sesostris III.|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt|de|12. Dynastie|12=draft|12=draft}}) in his seventh year of reign.

== Literature ==
* {{ill|Christian Leitz|fr|Christian Leitz|en|Christian Leitz|de|Christian Leitz|12=draft|12=draft}}: ''Altägyptische Sternuhren''. Peeters, Leuven 1995, ISBN 90-6831-669-9, p. 91.  
* {{ill|Alexandra von Lieven|fr|Alexandra von Lieven|de|Alexandra von Lieven|12=draft|12=draft}}: ''Grundriss des Laufes der Sterne – Das sogenannte Nutbuch''. The Carsten Niebuhr Institute of Ancient Eastern Studies (et al.), Copenhagen 2007, ISBN 978-87-635-0406-5, pp. 62–67 and 385.








